pv3199.math.structures

Class Vector

  • java.lang.Object
    • pv3199.math.structures.Vector

  • public class Vector
extends Object
    An immutable Euclidean vector. Vectors can be in the real or complex plane depending on how they are instantiated.

      • standard

        public static Vector standard(int space,
                              int dimensions)
        Produces a standard vector given the space index and the number of dimensions of the vector. For example, standard(0, 2) will produce a 2-dimensional vector that with its first scalar component set equal to 1 and the rest of the components equal to 0. Similarly, standard(2, 5) produces a 5-dimensional vector with its third component equal to 1. All standard vectors are unit, or have a magnitude of 1.
        Parameters:
        space - the space index.
        dimensions - the size of the vector.
        Returns:
        the standard vector based on the space index and number of dimensions.

      • forEachIndex

        public void forEachIndex(ConsumerHolder<Number> action)
        Iterates through each scalar component in this vector, applying a consumer that accepts a ForEachHolder containing the current scalar component value and current iterating index. If the consumer implementation does not need to access the indices for each iteration, it is advised to utilize forEach(Consumer).
        Parameters:
        action - the consumer action to apply on each scalar component value.

      • forEach
